Description: Fragment of handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine ginger-buff; few, mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Ion. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0369.18.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0381)
